encodeMessageDataForSafe(address,bytes).details: Returns the pre-image of the message hash (see {getMessageHashForSafe}).

params.safe: Safe to which the message is targeted.

encodeTransactionData(address,uint256,by.details: This method is added to the {CompatibilityFallbackHandler} for backwards compatibility with previous versions of Safe.      For a given Safe, the invariant `getTransactionHash(...) == keccak256(encodeTransactionData(...))` holds true.

params.baseGas: Base gas costs that are independent of the transaction execution (e.g. base transaction fee, signature check, payment of the refund).
params.data: Data payload of the Safe transaction.
params.gasPrice: Gas price that should be used for the payment calculation.
params.gasToken: Token address (or 0 for the native token) that is used for the payment.
params.operation: Operation type of the Safe transaction: 0 for `CALL` and 1 for `DELEGATECALL`.
params.refundReceiver: Address of receiver of the gas payment (or 0 for `tx.origin`).
params.safeTxGas: Gas that should be used for the Safe transaction.
params.to: Destination address of the Safe transaction.
params.value: Native token value of the Safe transaction.

getMessageHash(bytes).details: This function assumes that the caller is a Safe contract.

getMessageHashForSafe(address,bytes).details: Returns the hash of a message that can be signed by owners.

params.safe: Safe to which the message is targeted.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: This implementation verifies signatures for a `ISafe(msg.sender)`.

returns._0: The EIP-1271 magic value if the signature is valid, reverts otherwise.

simulate(address,bytes).details: Internally reverts execution to avoid side effects (making it effectively static).      Catches the internal revert and returns encoded result as bytes.      Inspired by <https://github.com/gnosis/util-contracts/blob/bb5fe5fb5df6d8400998094fb1b32a178a47c3a1/contracts/StorageAccessible.sol>.      ⚠️⚠️⚠️ This function assumes the caller is a Safe contract is only intended for being used as a fallback handler for a {Safe}.      Using it in other ways may cause undefined behavior. ⚠️⚠️⚠️

params.calldataPayload: Calldata that should be sent to the target contract (encoded method name and arguments).
params.targetContract: Address of the contract containing the code to execute.

tokensReceived(address,address,address,u.details: Account that wishes to receive the tokens also needs to register the implementer (this contract) via the ERC-1820 interface registry.      From the standard: "This is done by calling the setInterfaceImplementer function on the ERC-1820 registry with the holder address as      the address, the keccak256 hash of ERC777TokensSender (0x29ddb589b1fb5fc7cf394961c1adf5f8c6454761adf795e67fe149f658abe895) as the      interface hash, and the address of the contract implementing the ERC777TokensSender as the implementer."

encodeTransactionData(address,uint256,by.notice: Returns the pre-image of the Safe transaction hash (see {Safe.getTransactionHash}).

getMessageHash(bytes).notice: Returns the hash of a message to be signed by owners.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).notice: Implementation of the EIP-1271 signature validation method.

simulate(address,bytes).notice: Performs a `DELEGATECALL` to a `targetContract` in the context of self.
